  "texts": [
    "For human readers, it's better to give concrete examples and show action rather than explain what the reader should feel.",
    "This phenomenon is known as the \"show, not tell\" principle and doesn't always fit the way ChatGPT works: the chatbot generalizes huge amounts of information and provides ready-made solutions.",
    "For the time being, ChatGPT is not always able to generate authentic details; it's more common for the chatbot to combine data in different ways.",
    "However, the system is constantly being improved and updated, so new aspects of this issue require deeper research and study.",
    "It was also noticed that ChatGPT uses the same language passages regardless of the genre."
  ],
